<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span>tells us we are looking for the
side opposite the <img border="0" src="../images/6trigf3.JPG" width="26" height="19" align="middle"><span style="font-family:Arial">
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span>angle in the <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">m</b>edium
      triangle- </span></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<table border="0" width="100%">
  <tr>
    <td width="9%"><span style="font-family:Arial"> <span style="mso-text-raise:-6.0pt"><img border="0" src="../images/6trigf8.jpg" width="47" height="20"></span></span></td>
    <td width="64%">(top) <span style="font-family:Arial"> and opposite the <span style="mso-text-raise:-3.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf3.JPG" v:shapes="_x0000_i1035" width="26" height="19" align="middle"></span>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span>angle in the <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">s</b>mall
triangle- </span></td>
    <td width="27%"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span style="mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:Arial;color:yellow;mso-text-raise:-2.0pt"><img border="0" src="../images/6trigf1.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1036" width="26" height="19"></span></b><span style="font-family:Arial"><span style="mso-text-raise:-3.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf3.JPG" v:shapes="_x0000_i1037" width="26" height="19" align="middle"></span>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span>(bottom) <o:p>
      &nbsp;
</span></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<table border="0" width="100%">
  <tr>
    <td width="5%"><span style="font-family:Arial"><span style="mso-text-raise:
-13.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf9.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1038" width="16" height="47"></span>
      &nbsp;
</span></td>
    <td width="83%"><span style="font-family:Arial">tells us we are looking for the
side opposite the <span style="mso-text-raise:-2.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf10.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1039" width="13" height="15"></span>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span>angle in the medium triangle- <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">1&nbsp;
</b>
</span></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial">(top)<span style="font-family: Arial">,</span><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span> (which is the radius of the circle, <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">1</b>)
and the side opposite the <span style="mso-text-raise:-2.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf10.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1040" width="13" height="15"></span>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>angle in the small&nbsp;</span></p>
<table border="0" width="36%">
  <tr>
    <td width="12%"><span style="font-family:Arial"> triangle-&nbsp;</span></td>
    <td width="10%"> <span style="mso-text-raise:-6.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf11.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1041" width="49" height="21"></span></td>
    <td width="78%"><span style="font-family:Arial">(bottom)<o:p>
      &nbsp;</span></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial"> <span style="mso-text-raise:-6.0pt">
 </span>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial">&nbsp;<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial">So
<span style="mso-text-raise:-16.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf12.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1042" width="112" height="51" align="middle"></span>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span>and multiplying both sides of the
equation by <span style="mso-text-raise:-6.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf1.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1043" width="26" height="19" align="middle"></span><img border="0" src="../images/6trigf3.JPG" align="middle" width="26" height="19">
, we get<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span><o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal"><span style="font-family:Arial">Identity</span></b><span style="font-family:Arial">
#<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">1.</b> <span style="mso-text-raise:-16.0pt">
 </span><img border="0" src="../images/6trigf13.jpg" width="109" height="51">
<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial">This is our first identity
for trig, read as: <o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:14.0pt;font-family:Arial">the
tangent of alpha equals the sine of alpha divided by the cosine of alpha</span><span style="font-family:Arial">.<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial">&nbsp;<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial">Now see if you can make up
other proportions to get </span><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span style="font-family:Arial;color:blue">secant
</span></b><span style="font-family:
Arial"><span style="mso-text-raise:-3.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf3.JPG" v:shapes="_x0000_i1046" align="middle" width="26" height="19"></span>
, </span><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span style="font-family:Arial;color:#993300">cosecant
</span></b><span style="font-family:Arial"><span style="mso-text-raise:-3.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf3.JPG" v:shapes="_x0000_i1047" align="middle" width="26" height="19"></span>
, and </span><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span style="font-family:Arial;color:fuchsia">cotangent
</span></b><span style="font-family:Arial"><span style="mso-text-raise:-3.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf3.JPG" v:shapes="_x0000_i1048" align="middle" width="26" height="19"></span>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span>in terms of sin<span style="mso-text-raise:-3.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf3.JPG" v:shapes="_x0000_i1049" align="middle" width="26" height="19"></span>
 and/or cos<span style="mso-text-raise:-3.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf3.JPG" v:shapes="_x0000_i1050" align="middle" width="26" height="19"></span>
. You will get <o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial">&nbsp;<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal"><span style="font-family:Arial">Identity</span></b><span style="font-family:Arial">
#<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">2.</b> <span style="mso-text-raise:-16.0pt">
 </span><img border="0" src="../images/6trigf14.jpg" width="113" height="51">
 ,<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial">&nbsp;<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal"><span style="font-family:Arial">Identity</span></b><span style="font-family:Arial">
#<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">3.</b> <span style="mso-text-raise:-16.0pt">
 </span><img border="0" src="../images/6trigf15.jpg" width="107" height="51">
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span>,<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial">&nbsp;<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal"><span style="font-family:Arial">Identity</span></b><span style="font-family:Arial">
#<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">4.</b><o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial">If you use other
proportions, you can get other identities like <span style="mso-text-raise:
-16.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf17.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1054" width="113" height="51"></span>
.<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial">Make sure you can do these
yourself.<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial">&nbsp;<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial">Other important identities
can be obtained by using the Pythagorean theorem. <o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial">For example, in the <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">s</b>mall
triangle, <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">Identity</b> #<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">5</b> <span style="mso-text-raise:-7.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf18.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1055" width="171" height="32"></span>
. In the <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">m</b>edium triangle, <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Identity</b>
#<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">6</b> <span style="mso-text-raise:-7.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf19.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1056" width="172" height="32"></span>
and in the <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">L</b>arge triangle, <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Identity</b>
#<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">7</b> <span style="mso-text-raise:-7.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf20.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1057" width="169" height="32"></span>
. <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Identity</b> #<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">6</b>
can also be obtained from <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">Identity</b> #<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">1</b> by dividing each term by <span style="mso-text-raise:-7.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf21.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1058" width="69" height="32"></span>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span>and the third of these identities
can be obtained from <o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span style="font-family:Arial">Identity</span></b><span style="font-family:Arial">
#<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">1</b> by dividing each term by <span style="mso-text-raise:-7.0pt">
<img border="0" src="../images/6trigf22.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1059" width="64" height="32"></span>
.<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial">&nbsp;<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
